        "client_msg_id": "e45f56bc-bb1e-495f-af43-12d068954582",
        "text": "And speaking of agents, I don't think this is exactly what I was looking for, but I don't have a good Googleable query to get to a source.  So I asked agents.  Bard made up \"The Culture of Fudging in the U.S. Armed Forces\" by David Vine.  (That was enough to get me to something real.)  To follow up, I asked Chat GPT-3.5.  It gave generic advice on how to approach looking up the essay.  Also on Bard, there's a \"View other drafts\" dropdown that comes up with James Kitfield and James Mann as other people who might write this sort of thing.  Not helpful.  However, some have noticed that you can use variations like this to gauge the strength of believe in a LLM.",
